<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="791" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d791">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 894.001 M98/9.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>You will make to the Government of Japan appropriate expressions of the
                            sympathy of the President, the Government and the people of the United
                            States in the loss by the Japanese Empire of a ruler whose reign has
                            been so beneficent and distinguished. This will be in addition to the
                            messages which the President has sent to the new Emperor and to the
                            Empress Dowager, and my own cable to Viscount Uchida.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>